  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2025-02-18",
    "date": "2025-09-18T14:08:02Z",
    "text": "Cameron's Law\n\nThis bill increases the orphan drug tax credit to 50% (from 25%) of qualified clinical testing expenses paid or incurred in the development of drugs to treat certain rare diseases or conditions.\n\nAs background, the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act reduced the orphan drug tax credit (for tax years after 2017) to 25% of qualified clinical testing\u00a0expenses (e.g., wages, supplies, and certain contract expenses) paid or incurred in the development of drugs to treat certain rare diseases or conditions. For 2017 and prior tax years, the orphan tax credit was 50% of such expenses paid or incurred."
  },
